article.headline: American 71, Navy 49
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Andre Ingram had 15 points and Jason Thomas added 14 to lead American University past Navy 71-49 Tuesday night. American (12-11, 6-3, Patriot League) took a 13-10 lead when Thomas hit a 3-pointer with 12:02 remaining in the first half to start a 16-2 run that built a 26-12 Eagles advantage with 7:46 left in the first half. Navy (3-19, 0-9), which lost its 10th straight game for the first time since the 1988-89 season, never was able to cut the lead to fewer than seven points. When Jason Fernandez hit a 3-point shot with 8:47 to go, the Midshipmen trailed by 52-45. American ran off eight straight points, including two jumpers by Ingram to lead 60-45 with 6:27 left. It was the second game for Navy since coach Don DeVoe announced his retirement on Feb. 2. Navy's three wins this season have come against two Division III schools and Loyola (Md), which was in the midst of a 31-game losing streak. Chika Onyekanne led Navy with 12 points. American's coach, Jeff Jones won his 199th career game.
